__NOTOC__
== Configuring a cluster client ==

Here we describe how to configure an instance of {{PRODUCT}} to be a client in a [[Help:Scaleout | high-availability cluster]] setup. This client instance will then use the backend nodes combined into a cluster as its default triple store repository.

In order to enable the current {{PRODUCT}} instance to connect to the cluster DB as a client, the following properties have to be set:
<source>
# Enable start-up as cluster client. 
# The value must be "true"
scaleOutClusterClient=true
# Cluster seed node IPs. 
# Must be the same as the ones defined on the backend nodes.
clusterNodes=clusternode1\:47500..47529,clusternode2\:47500..47529
# Custom repository factory which initializes connection to the cluster backend using RMI calls. 
# Must be "class=com.fluidops.iwb.repository.fsail.FluidOpsRepositoryFactory"
repositoryType=class=com.fluidops.iwb.repository.fsail.FluidOpsRepositoryFactory
# Backend access credentials
ecmUserName=admin
ecmPasswordEnc=...
ecmServerUrl=http://localhost
</source>

You can use the configuration dialog below to configure these settings at runtime (* ''only visible when logged in with respective permissions'').

{{#widget: com.fluidops.iwb.widget.admin.InlineConfigurationWidget | 
 configOptions = {{ 'scaleOutClusterClient' | 'clusterNodes' | 'repositoryType' | 'ecmServerUrl' | 'ecmUserName' | 'ecmPasswordEnc' }}
}}